Key Match Events: The Sacramento Kings fell to the Los Angeles Clippers 107-98.
Sacramento shot an abysmal 3-of-26 (11.5 percent) from beyond the arc, compared to 14-of-30 (46.7 percent) for the Clippers.
De’Aaron Fox finished 2-of-5 and Keon Ellis 1-of-3 from three-point range.
The Kings finished with just 19 assists on 37 field goals.
